snippet.title: Marble Race Toy Unboxing Marble Mania Dual Speedway Kinder Playtime
snippet.description:
Today on Kinder Playtime we have another Marble Race Toy Unboxing!  Jacob loves Marble Races so much, he quickly asked to buy this toy when we saw it in the store.  It has entertained our kids for hours and this specific version can be found at Toys R Us location.  The one we bought this time is named the Techno Gears Marble Mania Dual Speedway Marble Race.

About the Techno Gears Marble Mania Dual Speedway Marble Race

In the olden days, kids raced one other using turtles scooped out of a pond or paper boats made out of their younger brother’s birth certificate. The Techno Gears Marble Mania Dual Speedway hosts race after thrilling race without requiring kids to leave the basement. Young racers launch their marble into a tubular speedway, waving crumpled dollar bills as their orb plummets past panoplies of breakneck turns and moveable contraptions. Hundreds of colorful pieces comprise the towering set, which includes an LED display and audible countdown to the race launch.

Marbles race one another in twin speedways
Hundreds of colorful construction pieces
Sound effects, including countdown to race launch
Trophy with LED display
Compete against friends or bogeymen bored of scaring you
Recommended for ages 8 and up
Requires two AA batteries (not included)
Dimensions (when assembled): 19.5”x5”x15.75”

This Marble Race set is pretty cool, but has some significant flaws.  None of the pieces really fit together all that well and need to be adjusted pretty frequently.  Kinder Playtime rates this toy a 3 out of 5 KP rating.
